    About

    Description

    Andy Warhol was an American visual artist, film director, producer, and leading figure in the pop art movement. Wikipedia
    Born: August 6, 1928, Pittsburgh, PA
    Died: February 22, 1987, New York Presbyterian Hospital, New York, NY
    Periods: Pop art, Modern art
    Influenced by: Marcel Duchamp, Jasper Johns, Tom of Finland, Ben Shahn, Jack Smith
    Parents: Andrej Warhola, Julia Warhola
    Influenced: Jean-Michel Basquiat, Nico, Takashi Murakami, MORE
